race.comment: It's hard to knock the form of the well-related PRESSZORA (4) (half to G2 winner Amor Victorious) who has won five of six starts to date and is racing with a lot of confidence. Drawn to sit up on speed from the inside marble and should give backers a big sight. ROYAL GLADIATOR (8) got the job done over this distance range at the Sunny Coast last time out and winning rider Collis stays on top. Big chance once again. EL FORTRESS (9) has a handy record here on his home circuit with a win and two seconds from just four spins. Top-three aspirations. SMASHING ROSIE (11) gets in well at the weights with the 3kg claim and looks a must for the exotics players. BOOM BOOM RAY (5) also hails from a handy family (half to G2 winner Doull) and can feature with any luck from the carpark draw.
